  "texts": [
    "Choosing κ = 2βγ, we deduce from Theorem 3.3, that the estimator x based on counting occurrence of blow-up motifs G κ,γ, ᾱ/ β recovers the communities with probability at least 1 -1/n as long as λ ≥ w ′′ r ϵ -5 log 1/r (n)",
    "The corresponding polynomial has a degree of the order ϵr.",
    "In particular, if we take ϵ = log(log(n))/ log(n), we establish that, for any irrational r, it is possible to recover the communities above the threshold (2) with a polynomial of degree O(log(n)/ log(log(n))).",
    "Whether this polynomial can be computed (or wellapproximated) in polynomial-time remains an open question.",
    "4 Proof of Proposition 3.1"
